{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "plt.style.use('bmh')\n",
    "\n",
    "# custom figure styles\n",
    "from plot_style import std_fig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Random linear classifiers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Hyperplanes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "a hyperplane is a set of the form $\\{x\\,|\\, a^T x = b\\}$ where $a, x\\in \\mathbb{R}^n$ and where $b\\in \\mathbb{R}$.\n",
    "\n",
    "There are a few geometric interpretations of the hyperplane $\\{x\\,|\\, a^T x = b\\}$\n",
    "- if $b=0$, then this is the set of all vectors that are orthogonal to $a$; that is, the solution can be thought of as the plane defined by the normal vector $a$.\n",
    "- if $b\\neq 0$, then the plane in the $b=0$ case is offset from the origin. We can think of it like\n",
    "    \n",
    "$$\\{x\\,|\\, a^Tx - b = 0\\} = \\{x \\,|\\, a^T(x - x_0) = 0\\} $$\n",
    "    \n",
    "where $x_0$ is any vector such that $a^T x_0 = b$. This makes sense, because *any* element of the original offset hyperplane can be subtracted to recover the hyperplane passing through the origin.\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"../img/6.036_hyperplane.png\" width=300>\n",
    "\n",
    "The perpendicular offset of the origin $d$ can be computed by noting that the vector $\\mathbf{0} + da$ lies on the hyperplane. Hence\n",
    "$$\n",
    "a^T(0 + d a) = b \\Rightarrow d = \\frac{b}{a^T a}\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "θ, b = np.array([3, 4]), 5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if $a^T x + b = 0$, then $a_1 x + a_2 y + b = 0 $ hence \n",
    "$$ y = -\\frac{1}{a_2}(a_1 x +b )$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We plot the example to show we are correct."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 288x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x = np.linspace(-2, 1, 50); y = - 1/θ[1]*(θ[0]*x + b)\n",
    "\n",
    "# draw hyperplane\n",
    "with std_fig() as (fig, ax): \n",
    "    ax.plot(x,y)\n",
    "    ax.plot(x, np.zeros_like(x), 'k')\n",
    "    ax.plot(np.zeros_like(x), x, 'k')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # draw distance to line\n",
    "    d = b/np.dot(θ,θ)\n",
    "    α = np.linspace(0, -d, 20)\n",
    "    x = α*θ[0]; y = α*θ[1]\n",
    "    ax.plot(x, y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## signed distance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let ppp be an arbitrary point in $\\mathbb{R}^d$. Give a formula for the signed perpendicular distance from the hyperplane specified by $\\theta, \\theta_0$, to this point $p$.\n",
    "<img src=\"../img/6.036_signed_dist.png\" width=300>\n",
    "\n",
    "Let $d$ be the signed distance we seek. Note that $(p - \\theta d)$ is on the hyperplane. Hence $\\theta^T(p + \\theta d) + \\theta_0 = 0$ and we have \n",
    "\n",
    "$$d = \\frac{\\theta^T p + \\theta_0}{\\theta^T \\theta} $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def signed_dist(x, θ, b):\n",
    "    return ( np.dot(θ, x) + b )/np.dot(θ,θ)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def classify(x, θ, b):\n",
    "    signs = np.sign(signed_dist(x, θ, b))\n",
    "    return signs.astype(int)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Get the signed distance and classify a set of random points according to our hyperplane."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "N = 200\n",
    "xr = np.random.rand(N) - 1.1\n",
    "yr = np.random.rand(N) - 1.3\n",
    "D = np.array([xr, yr])\n",
    "sd = signed_dist(D, θ, b)\n",
    "classification = classify(D, θ, b)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "with std_fig(1, 2, figsize=(8,4)) as (fig, ax):\n",
    "    x = np.linspace(-1.5, 0.5, 50); y = - 1/θ[1]*(θ[0]*x + b)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # draw hyperplane\n",
    "    for axis in ax:\n",
    "        axis.plot(x,y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    lim = 0.1\n",
    "    ax[0].scatter(xr, yr, c=sd, cmap='seismic', s=10, vmin=-lim, vmax=lim)\n",
    "    ax[1].scatter(xr, yr, c=classification, cmap='coolwarm', s=10, vmin=-1, vmax=1)\n",
    "    ax[0].set_title('signed distance from hyperplane'); ax[1].set_title('classification')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Creating a random linear classifier"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In creating a linear classfier, we need a way to score the classifier. Here, we simply return the number of testing data that were correctly classified."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def score(data, labels, θ, b):\n",
    "    classifications = classify(data, θ, b)\n",
    "    correct = (classifications == labels)\n",
    "    return np.sum(correct)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def best_separator(data, labels, Thetas, bs):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    :param Thetas: shape (m, d) each row is a θ candidate\n",
    "    :param bs: shape (m,) bs to go with each θ\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    scores = np.zeros_like(bs)\n",
    "    for idx, (θ, b) in enumerate(zip(Thetas, bs)):\n",
    "        scores[idx] = score(data, labels, θ, b)\n",
    "    max_idx = np.argmax(scores)\n",
    "    return Thetas[max_idx], bs[max_idx], scores, max_idx "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_random_separators(d, m, b_range=10):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    :param d: dimension of problem\n",
    "    :param m: number of separators returned\n",
    "    :returns Theta: (m, d) matrix of random separators\n",
    "    :returns bs: (m,) vectors of offsets\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Theta = np.random.random((m, d)) - 0.5 # random vectors around origin\n",
    "    bs = np.random.random(m) * b_range\n",
    "    return Theta, bs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we are ready to randomly generate a linear classifier. We will see if we can generate something that matches the classifier above."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trials = 1500\n",
    "Th, bs = generate_random_separators(d=2, m=trials)\n",
    "θ_best, b_best, scores, max_idx = best_separator(D, classification, Th, bs)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x = np.linspace(-1.5, 0.5, 50); y = - 1/θ[1]*(θ[0]*x + b)\n",
    "yb = - 1/θ_best[1]*(θ_best[0]*x + b_best)\n",
    "\n",
    "with std_fig(1, 2, figsize=(8,4)) as (fig, ax):\n",
    "    # draw hyperplane\n",
    "    for axis in ax:\n",
    "        axis.scatter(xr, yr, c=classification, cmap='coolwarm', s=10, vmin=-1, vmax=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax[1].plot(x,y, 'k')\n",
    "    ax[0].plot(x, yb, 'g')\n",
    "    ax[0].set_title('best classifier'); ax[1].set_title('perfect classification')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "However, this is quite expensive; our classifier is not perfect, even after 1500 trials."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Perceptrons"
   ]
